-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1680594068361"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1680594068342" data-id="1680594068342"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675760058653" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675760058653"><div class="elm text-edit gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000">Established in 1887, the Mitsubishi Pencil Company produces innovative products of exceptional quality. Virtually all of their normal writing pens feature waterproof and fade-resistant pigment ink - superior in performance to the dyestuff inks used in most pens, and highly resistant to tampering or accidental spillages. The ever-growing Uni-ball series of rollerball pens has long been renowned for smooth writing characteristics, elegant design and high quality ink, notably the classic <a href="https://cultpens.com/collections/uni-ball-eye" class="">Uni-ball Eye</a>. These are now joined by products such as the <a href="https://cultpens.com/collections/uni-jetstream" class="">Jetstream</a> range of class-leading hybrid ink pens; <a href="https://cultpens.com/collections/uni-posca-markers" class="">POSCA markers</a> with their brilliant water-based inks; and the highly useful <a href="https://cultpens.com/collections/uni-powertank" class="">PowerTank</a> which features a pressurised refill. Manufacturer Sites: <a href="http://www.uniball.co.uk/" class="" target="_blank">Uni-Ball UK</a> - <a href="http://www.mpuni.co.jp/" class="" target="_blank">Uni-Ball Japan</a></font></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1